case_circumstances: On 5/26/1987, a hunter found a body lying in the woods 40 feet from State Highway @W nine miles north of Interstate 70, Warrenton, Warren County, Missouri.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body:
Dark blue t shirt with a silk screen printing on the front of the shirt with five blooming red and white roses, 1987 Rose Bowl Pasadena, California, Michigan Wolverines Big Ten Champions.  Also on the front left side of the shirt was a Wolverine logo, yellow and white in color, with red and white stemmed roses in its teeth.  Nothing on the back of the shirt.

Designer blue jeans - Oscar De La Renta - unknown size.  Jeans had been hemmed up approximately 2" and were frayed at the ends.  White Jockey underwear,
case_footwear: J.C. Penney brand white crew socks. Victim was wearing what appeared to be new NIKE high-top tennis shoes, size 9.
dental: Dental information / charting is currently not available
documents: There are currently no documents available for this case.
